Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    private boolean isRaining = false;
    private boolean isCloudy = false;
    private int temperature = 20; // In Celsius

    public void changeWeather(boolean clouds, boolean rain) {
        if (clouds) {
            isCloudy = true;
            if (rain) {
                isRaining = true;
                temperature -= 5;
            }
        } else {
            isCloudy = false;
            if (!rain) {
                isRaining = false;
                temperature += 3;
            }
        }
    }

    public boolean isItRaining() {
        return isRaining;
    }

    public int getTemperature() {
        return temperature;
    }
}",

If we simulate a scenario with clouds but no rain, will the temperature necessarily increase?
